metadata.job_to_be_done: Prepare a vegetarian buffet-style dinner menu for a corporate gathering, including gluten-free items.

extracted_sections.section_title: Rau Muong Xao Toi (Stir-Fried Morning Glory with Garlic)

subsection_analysis.refined_text: : o Mix ground beef, ground pork, diced onion, minced garlic, breadcrumbs, beaten egg, paprika, salt, and pepper in a bowl. o Form mixture into meatballs. o Heat olive oil in a pan and brown meatballs on all sides. o Add tomato sauce and simmer for 20 minutes. o Serve warm.

 1 pound ground beef  1 small onion, diced  2 cloves garlic, minced  1 carrot, grated  1 celery stalk, diced  1 can (28 ounces) crushed tomatoes  1/4 cup tomato paste  1/2 cup red wine (optional)  1 teaspoon dried oregano  1 teaspoon dried basil  Salt and pepper to taste  Spaghetti for serving  Grated Parmesan cheese for garnish.

 1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined  4 cloves garlic, minced  1/4 cup white wine  1/4 cup chicken broth  1/4 cup lemon juice  1/4 cup butter  2 tablespoons olive oil  1/4 cup chopped parsley  Salt and pepper to taste  Cooked pasta for serving.

: o Dice fish or shrimp and place in a bowl. o Pour lime juice over the seafood and let marinate for 30 minutes. o Dice onion, tomatoes, and jalapeño. o Chop cilantro. o Mix all ingredients together and add salt. o Serve chilled.

 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts  1/2 cup spinach, chopped  1/2 cup feta cheese, crumbled  1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes, chopped  2 cloves garlic, minced  2 tablespoons olive oil  Salt and pepper to taste.

: o Sauté diced onion, carrots, celery, and minced garlic until softened. o Add diced zucchini, tomatoes, and broth. o Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes. o Add beans and pasta, cook until pasta is tender. o Stir in chopped basil and serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
